2026-05-17 19:21:48 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #1 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] submit_repaired_code({"code": "import pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nbase = Path('kramabench-environment-hard-9/files')\npaths = {\n    'Malibu': base / 'malibu_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    'Tenean': base / 'tenean_beach_datasheet.csv',\n    'Wollaston': base / 'wollaston_beach_datasheet.csv',\n}\n\n\ndef load_and_check(path):\n    # Files use a title row, then a second row with beach/location labels, then headers.\n    df = pd.read_csv(path, skiprows=1, header=[0, 1])\n\n    cols = df.columns.to_frame(index=False)\n    cols.iloc[:, 0] = cols.iloc[:, 0].replace(r'^Unnamed.*', pd.NA, regex=True).ffill()\n\n    flat_cols = []\n    for top, bottom in cols.itertuples(index=False, name=None):\n        parts = []\n        for part in (top, bottom):\n            if pd.isna(part):\n                continue\n            s = str(part).strip()\n            if s and s.lower() != 'nan' and not s.startswith('Unnamed:'):\n                parts.append(s)\n        flat_cols.append('_'.join(parts) if parts else 'unknown')\n    df.columns = flat_cols\n\n    date_col = 'Date' if 'Date' in df.columns else df.columns[0]\n    ent_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'Enterococcus' in c]\n    if not ent_cols:\n        return False\n\n    m = df.melt(id_vars=[date_col], value_vars=ent_cols, value_name='Enterococcus')\n    m['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(m[date_col], errors='coerce')\n    m = m[(m['Date'] >= pd.Timestamp('2020-01-01')) & (m['Date'] <= pd.Timestamp('2024-12-31'))]\n\n    m['Enterococcus_num'] = pd.to_numeric(m['Enterococcus'], errors='coerce')\n    numeric = m['Enterococcus_num'].dropna()\n    return bool(len(numeric) > 0 and (numeric < 104).all())\n\n\nresults2 = {}\nfor name, path in paths.items():\n    ok = load_and_check(path)\n    results2[name] = ok\n    print(name, ok)\n\nprint('RESULTS2', results2)", "reason": "Rewrote the code to work with the actual sandbox files and their two-row header structure. It now checks the same three beach datasheets (Malibu, Tenean, Wollaston), computes whether all numeric Enterococcus samples from 2020-2024 are below 104, prints each boolean, and prints the final results dict."}) [toolUseId=call_M2cW0milTaaPj0lnix3ylLwm]
